notes: Data from Coral Reef Ecosystem Division (CRED), NOAA Pacific Islands Fisheries Science Center (PIFSC) Subsurface Temperature and Pressure Recorders (STPR) provide a time series of water temperature and sea level pressure at coral reef sites. Data is typically collected at 1800 second intervals for a duration of 2 years using a SBE39 Temperature Recorder with Pressure Sensor (Sea-Bird Electronics, Inc., www.seabird.com). When a STPR is recovered, a new one is typically deployed in the same place. Time series data combining multiple deployments from a given site may also be available. Please contact CRED with any questions. For program information see the web site https://www.pifsc.noaa.gov/cred/ocean_and_climate_change.php
